    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Maybe `pandas.DataFrame.from_series(cls, data, orient='columns', dtype=None)`?\n\ndata = list of pandas.Series.\n\nOrder is set inherently and column names or index values (depending on _orient_) can be extracted from the series (or set to default values when not available)\n\nlines up with;\n- pandas.DataFrame.from_csv\n- pandas.DataFrame.from_dict\n- pandas.DataFrame.from_records\n\nI am not a big fan off _one does it all_ `__init__`.\n"
  },
